From: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
Subject: [PATCH] ARM: dts: omap4-steelhead: set BT HCI UART max-speed = 3 Mbaud

The BCM4330 Bluetooth HCI runs over UART2. Without a `max-speed` property the
hci_bcm driver leaves oper_speed = 0 and never synchronises the host UART to the
baud the BCM4330 firmware operates at, so the two ends drift apart. On device
this manifests as a stream of "Bluetooth: hci0: Frame reassembly failed (-84)"
(EILSEQ — corrupted HCI bytes), HCI command tx timeouts, a phantom "Connected"
state that does not reflect reality, and A2DP audio arriving in corrupt bursts
(~1 s of sound then several seconds of silence). The phone ultimately drops the
link (HCI reason 0x13, remote-user-terminated).

The stock Android kernel ran the steelhead BT UART at 3 Mbaud (the baud that
dominates the stock image). Set the same operating speed so hci_bcm commands
both the controller and the host UART to 3 Mbaud and the link is clean. Hardware
flow control (RTS/CTS) is already muxed in uart2_pins.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
---
 arch/arm/boot/dts/ti/omap/omap4-steelhead.dts | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/ti/omap/omap4-steelhead.dts
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/ti/omap/omap4-steelhead.dts
@@ -524,6 +524,13 @@
 		compatible = "brcm,bcm4330-bt";
 		pinctrl-names = "default";
 		pinctrl-0 = <&bt_pins>;
+		/* Operating HCI UART baud. Without it hci_bcm leaves oper_speed=0 and
+		 * never syncs the host UART to the BCM4330 firmware rate -> host and
+		 * controller drift -> "hci0: Frame reassembly failed (-84)" (EILSEQ),
+		 * command tx timeouts, phantom Connected state, A2DP audio in corrupt
+		 * bursts. Stock ran the BT UART at 3 Mbaud; match it. RTS/CTS muxed in
+		 * uart2_pins. (2026-07-08 BT-audio investigation.) */
+		max-speed = <3000000>;
 		shutdown-gpios = <&gpio2 14 GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH>; /* gpio_46 BT_EN */
 		reset-gpios = <&gpio2 20 GPIO_ACTIVE_LOW>; /* gpio_52 BT_RESET */
 		device-wakeup-gpios = <&gpio2 13 GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH>; /* gpio_45 BT_WAKE */
